A special meeting of the Financial Stability and Development Committee of the State Council was held to address the current economic and capital market challenges. At the critical moment, this meeting responded to important issues including volatile Chinese stocks and the oversight of platform companies. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zheng Junfeng analyzes how Chinese regulators juggle in being adaptive to the ever-changing market needs, as they strive to boost the healthy development of the capital market.